Constructor Detail

Person

public Person()
Default constructor. Must be called to initialise the object's member variables. The constructor sets the name and email of this person to empty String, while the date of birth is given today's date. The id field is set to current time when the object is created.

setName

public void setName(java.lang.String name)
Assigns a new name to the person.

Calling this method will invoke the propertyChange(java.beans.PropertyChangeEvent) method on all registered PropertyChangeListener objecs. The PropertyChangeEvent passed with the PropertyChangeListener.propertyChange(java.beans.PropertyChangeEvent) method has the following characteristics:

  • the getNewValue() method returns a String with the newly assigned name
  • the getOldValue() method returns a String with the person's old name
  • the getPropertyName() method returns a String with the value NAME_PROPERTY_NAME.
